Management to direct the Municipal Accountant to:

Issue demand letters to all accountable officials/personnel with outstanding receivables particularly those of more than four years, and exhaust all means to collect dormant receivable accounts;

Strictly comply with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016 and COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated November 28, 2012 on the required analysis of dormant accounts in performing the regular and periodic verification, analysis, and validation of the existence of the receivables, unliquidated cash advances, and determine the concerned debtors, accountable officers (Regular and Special Disbursing Officers, Collecting Officers, Cashiers) for strict monitoring and disposition of said accounts;

Provide allowance for impairment for dormant receivables and cash advances accounts in oder to have a fair presentation of the financial statements as required under PPSAS 29. Compute/ determine impairment in accordance with the Philippine Public Sector Accounting Standards or Philippine Financial Reporting Standards; and

Comply with all the conditions and requirements of COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016 for the possible request for the write-off of the specified dormant receivables and cash advances accounts particularly of all deceased Accountable Officers to the Commission on Audit.

We reiterated our prior years’ audit recommendations that Management through the Municipal Planning and Development Council, Municipal Engineering Office and other concerned offices to:

Conduct proper planning including timing and execution of priority projects of the LGU;

Expedite the implementation of the development projects funded out of the 20% Development Fund in accordance with the guidelines set forth under DILG and DBM Joint Circular No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017;


Establish strict monitoring control over projects to ensure timely completion of the same;

Ensure full and optimum utilization of the fund in order to attain the desired socio-economic and environmental outcomes; and

To start the bidding process after the approval of the annual budget based on the attached PPMP.

