We reiterated our previous audit recommendations that the Municipal Mayor:

Direct the MPDC to submit the final and complete Accomplishment Reports on PPAs for CY 2018;

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prepare and maintain a Monthly Monitoring Report to keep track of the progress of all PPAs within his power/ jurisdiction from planning stage to implementation to completion since it is one of the duties of the Municipal Engineer to “administer, coordinate, supervise, and control the construction, maintrnance, improvement, repair of roads, bridges, and other engineering and public works projects of the local government unit concerned” pursuant to Section 477 of RA 7160 for consolidation by the MPDC;

Direct the Project Heads/ Managers of all non-infrastructure PPAs to prepare and maintain a Monthly Monitoring Report for consolidation byt the MPDC;

Direct all Project Heads/ Managers to coordinate with the Municipal Accuntant and Municipal Budget Officer on the costs incurred of the projects for inclusion in their Montly Monitoring Report; and

Require all Project Heads/ Managers and other concerned officials to coordinate with the MPDCand adhere strictly tp the provisions of COA Circular No. 2013-004 dated January 30, 2013.

Require the Municipal Budget Officer, Municipal Planning and Development Officer (MPDO), Bids and Awards Committee (BAC), and Municipal Accountant to review the prior years’ obligations under the SEF and the availability of such fund balances in the depository bank;

After determining the fund balances in the bank, and in order to maximize the utilization of related funds, consider the following courses of action:

Revert the unobligated/ unexpended appropriations of completed projects for re-appropriation to other priority projects;

Require the MPDO to revisit the unfunded priority projects in the Work and Financial Plan or propose new projects for the consideration thereof in the re-appropriation of the unappropriated surplus;

Request the Sangguniang Bayan to pass the related resolutions on the budget to be funded from the unappropriated surplus for the specific priority projects for implementation; and

Execute without delay such projects which are determined to still address the present needs of the intended student-beneficiaries.

