We recommended that the municipality undertake the following measures to address the delays in the procurement process and submission of documents to support its obligations: 

a. Discontinue practice of earmarking funds for transactions without valid and complete documentation;

b. Require the Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Accountant to review supporting documents and reconcile records on a monthly basis to arrive at reliable amounts of allotments available for obligation and fair presentation of obligations of the LGU in the financial statements;

c. Designate alternate BAC members to ensure continuity of duties for each of the procurement process; and

d. Establish procurement timelines in consonance with project schedules, including a cut-off date for processing requisitions and issuance of purchase orders to ensure timely receipt of most of the procured items for the project implementation, with provisions for exceptions only in cases of emergencies.

