We recommended that the management:

a. Direct the Municipal Accountant to reconcile the difference  in balances between the Philhealth Per Family Payment Rate Disposition and Allocation Form and the Subsidiary Ledger;

b. Refrain from charging disbursements not allowable in the said PFPR fund;

c. Direct the Municipal Health Office and Office of the Municipal Accountant to maintain records reflecting the charges and balances for every allocation provided in said Philhealth Circular;

d. Efficiently utilize PFPR fund accordingly for which they are intended to ensure that indigent members have better access to quality health services of the LGU.

Recommendations:

We recommended that management: 

a.  Require the Municipal Treasurer to duly execute all contracts of lease for all existing occupants and submit to us copies of the same within thirty (30) days from receipt thereof;

b. Concerned LGU officials should exert extra efforts to intensify collection of delinquent accounts and adopt all necessary measures to enable the collections of unpaid stall rentals and formulate plans and adopts policies and strategies relative to the vacant stalls in the public market with the end view of generating more income from them;

